node.text:
What we have seen over the past few months has been unprecedented 😱

While crisis' can be incredibly scary, they are also filled with the most amount of opportunity. If you know how and why things happen in the economy and financial markets then you can set yourself up for growth during this time📈

We are currently experiencing a liquidity crisis. This causes asset prices to drop and currency values to increase (deflation). The Fed and Treasury does 2 things to combat this deflation:
1) print money
2) lower interest rates

This marginally helps liquidity in the short run. In the medium to long-run it causes inflation when asset prices rise and currency values fall meaning your money becomes less valuable📉

Opportunity presents itself as we (likely) move from a liquidity crisis to a financial crisis aka recession😳

As asset prices continue to fall, it is your job as an investor to move from cash/credit into assets prior to the rise in inflation.

Intelligent investors will move into inflation hedged assets such as:
- real estate
- precious metals
- bitcoin

This is also a great time to go purchase distressed businesses (stocks) and/or businesses that are undervalued due to the emotional reaction of this pandemic.

I am personally moving much more of my cash into bitcoin as I see this asset turning into a long-term store of value that will greatly outperform gold as the supply is cut by 50% once again this month from the halving🚀

Go watch the full 20 min video on YouTube. I know you will get tons of value💰

What are you doing with your wealth during this crisis and possible recession ahead of us?👇🏻

node.text:
The cool thing to do for many entrepreneurs that have "made it" is to go buy brand new exotic cars with cash 💰

This could not be further from cool when you consider it is a $3,000,000 mistake (just from $100k purchase) from the opportunity cost of the money they spend. And it is actually much higher when you factor in the taxes and all the other benefits I discuss in the video🤷🏼‍♂️ People do things like this just to increase their worth in the perception of others. I have done this before as well and can tell you it did not make me happier or wealthier 👎🏻 I challenge you to start asking yourself before every financial decision: does this make logical financial sense? Or am I doing this based on emotion? 🧐

When you make decisions that are truly the best thing for you and your unique values, that is when you will be really happy/healthy/financially abundant 💯

Go watch the rest on my YouTube channel I promise you’ll get immense value from the 9 minute video🔥

Let me know your thoughts below👇🏻

node.title: Buying A Car Is A $3,000,000 Mistake! 👎🏻

💰Top 3 things to understand to become financially independent 💰

1) credit- will not only save you tens of thousands of dollars but will also allow you to scale in business much quicker, avoid capital gains tax and do cool things like travel for free

2) investments - you must find ways to at least outperform inflation. If you do not, you will consistently lose the hard earned value (money) you worked for

3) taxes - are your biggest expense. There are many ways to avoid and lower them legally. Starting a business, owning real estate, assisting with energy production and pretty much anything that provides resources to other people and businesses is tax advantaged because the government wants to incentive people to produce resources, value and hospitality for the people of the country

What would you make #4 on this list? 🤔

* I am not a tax advisor or a financial planner. Just a human sitting in a lambo on this rock we call earth 😁

node.text:
Ever wonder why your credit scores are so different?

It’s because there are over 10 FICO credit scores used on 3 different bureaus😲

And there are different scores that are weighted differently depending on if you’re checking a score used for mortgages, cars or credit cards 💳 

Some of these scores even go up to 900!

It’s best to check the right score before applying to certain types of debt. For example:

Check:

FICO 5 for a mortgage
FICO Auto 8 for a car
FICO Bankcard 8 for credit cards

You can also ask the lender prior to applying what bureau and type of credit score they will pull so you have an idea. 

Go check your real credit scores on something like myFICO.com or creditchecktotal.com

Did you know this about credit scores? 🤔

Most people spend way more than they think when buying #crypto

When you go buy on an app like coinbase, they can:
1) charge up to a 15% fee (cost is higher when buying smaller amounts
2) they allow for 10% slippage so if your order moves the market or the market moves quickly, you could be paying 10% higher than the price you saw
3) they also charge everyone a “consumer exchange rate” fee which they do not disclose the exact amount because “it varies”

If you want to dramatically reduce these fees go use:

Pro.Coinbase.com

Binance.us

Or any other site or app that allows you to set “limit orders”

Limit orders will allow you to avoid almost all of these fees above and you’ll know exactly what price you are buying the asset at!

Share this with someone that needs to hear this! 💰

Want a better credit score?

To get:
A house
A car
Fund a new business idea
Or hack the credit card rewards system to travel for free?

Well few people actually know what’s most important in the credit game…

After helping thousands of people with credit, here is some important information most people do not know:

Other than the obvious of don’t carry too much personal debt and pay your bills on time, you should focus on:

1) getting over 21 personal accounts that are different types of accounts (credit cards, personal loans, auto loans and a mortgage (if you need a house)). 
2) getting as many on time payments on those accounts as possible. Make small purchases on the accounts and set them up to pay the statement balance each month.

You do this because the payment history behind your score is more important than your score itself!
